quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  31,1,Alif; Lam. Mim
  31,2,These are verses of the Wise Book
  31,3,A guidance and a mercy for the well-doers
  31,4,Those who establish the prayer and give the poor-rate and of the Hereafter are convinced
  31,5,"These are on guidance from their Lord, and these! they are the blissful ones"
  31,6,"And of mankind is one who purchaseth an idle discourse, that he may mislead from Allah's way without knowledge, and taketh it by way of mockery. These! for them shall be a torment ignominious"
  31,7,"And when Our revelations are recited unto him he turneth away in his stiff-neckedness as though he heard them not: as though there was a deafness in his ears. So announce thou unto him a torment afflictive"
  31,8,"Verily those who believe and work righteous works, theirs shall be Gardens of Delight"
  31,9,"Therein they will be abiders: a true promise of Allah. And He is the Mighty, the Wise"
  31,10,He hath created the heavens that ye behold without pillars and hath cast Into the earth firm mountains lest it move away with you; and He hath scattered thereon every kind of animal. And We send down water from the heaven and We make grow every kind of goodly growth therein
  31,11,This is the creation of Allah; shew that which those beside Him me have created. Aye! the wrong-doers are in error manifest